Executive Profile
Christopher Harwood Bernard Mills  Chief Executive Officer, Investment Manager, and Director, North Atlantic Smaller Companies Investment Trust PLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 28 Board Members in 28 different organizations across 37 different industries.See Board Relationships63--
Background

		Mr. Christopher Harwood Bernard Mills, also known as Chris, serves as the Chief Executive Officer and Partner at Harwood Capital LLP. Mr. Mills founded Harwood Capital Management Limited in 2011 and serves as its Chief Executive. He serves as Chief Executive Officer and Investment Manager of North Atlantic Smaller Companies Investment Trust PLC. He is a Managing Partner at Harwood Private Equity. Mr. Mills serves as a founder of Harwood Real Estate Limited in 2009. He ... served as Chief Investment Officer of Harwood Capital LLP. He was the Chief Investment Officer and Director of J O Hambro Capital Management Limited, which he co-founded in 1993. Mr. Mills was employed at Montagu Investment Management and Invesco Ltd. as an Investment Manager from 1975 to 1993. He served as Head of North American Investments and North American Venture Capital and Director of Samuel Montagu Limited. Previously, Mr. Mills worked at HSBC Private Bank (UK) Limited. Previously, he was a Principal at Garrison Investment Management Limited and was employed at HSBC Republic Bank (UK) Limited and as an Executive Officer at Steel City Products, LLC. He was Managing Partner of Trident Private Equity Fund II, L.P. Previously; he was the Chief Investment Officer at Leisure & Media VCT. Mr. Mills has been a Non-Executive Chairman of EKF Diagnostics Holdings plc since April 08, 2016. He has been Non-Executive Director of Quantum Pharma Plc since October 19, 2016. He has been Director of Oryx International Growth Fund Ltd. since December 3, 1994. He has been a Non-Executive Director of Cyprotex plc since August 24, 2013. He has been a Director of SunLink Health Systems Inc. since July 11, 2007. He has been a Non-Executive Director of Catalyst Media Group Plc since June 1, 2007. He serves as a Director of MJ Gleeson Group Limited. He serves as Non-Executive Director of Acquisitor Holdings Ltd. He has been Chairman at Grovebirch PLC since June 13, 2003. He has been a Director of LESCO, Inc. since May 2000. He has been Non-Executive Director of Bioquell plc since December 18, 2012, AssetCo plc since March 23, 2011, Goals Soccer Centers plc since May 5, 2016 and Essenden PLC since May 26, 2009. Mr. Mills has been a Non-Executive Director of Nationwide Accident Repair Services Limited since June 4, 2009. He has been a Director of Compass Plastics & Technologies, Inc. and AB Plastics since September 1996. Mr. Mills has been a Non-Executive Director of Journey Group plc since January 5, 2015 and Grovebirch PLC since January 2002. He serves as a Director of Oak Industries Inc. He has been a Director of PS Group Holdings, Inc. since 1996. Mr. Mills serves as a Director of P.S. Group Holdings Inc., Harwood Real Estate Limited and Denison Hydraulics, Inc. He serves as Director of HCG Corporate Advisers Limited. Mr. Mills serves as a Non-Executive Director of Harwood Wealth Management Group Plc since March 29, 2016 and Izodia plc since April 22, 2003. He has been Director of MJ Gleeson PLC since January 1, 2009. He serves as a Director of Celsis International Ltd. since 2009. He serves as Director of Calenden Limited, Cross-Border Publishing Limited, Autotag Limited, Lindley Catering Limited and Checkout Holdings Limited. Mr. Mills is a Director of American Plastic Technologies Inc., Avanti Inc., CelluTissue Industries, Copy Duplicating Products Inc., Magic Seasoning Blends Inc., PNG Corporation, W-H Holdings Inc., and J O Hambro Capital Management Group Limited, Consolidated Venture Finance Limited, Growth Financial Services Limited, Cross Border Limited, Hampton Investment Properties Limited, Catalyst Media holdings Limited, Alternateport Limited, Satellite Information Services (Holdings) Limited, 62 Pont Street (Freehold) Limited, Alba Investment Properties Limited, Alba Investment Properties holdings Limited, Harwood Capital management Limited, Harwood Capital Nominees Limited, Kelvinhaugh Student Accommodation Limited, Team Rock Limited, Stratton Street (Anthony) Limited, Harwood Multi Manager Limited, Glass America, Inc, Progeny, Inc, Global Options Group, Inc and Performance Chemicals Company. He is the Non-Executive Director of Ten Entertainment Group plc. He serves as Director of B&G (Europe) Holding Ltd., BDBCO No. 859 Limited, Indoor Bowling Equity Limited, Indoor Bowling Acquisitions Limited, Stratton Street (Mouse No.1) Limited, Tramworks Limited, IR Media Group Limited, Hardwood Holdco Growth Financial Services Limited, GlobalOptions Group, Inc, Performance Chemicals Company Investments Limited, B&G Equipment Co, Tagos Group GTL Resources Limited, Winnfield Holding Corporation and Utitec. He was Non-Executive Chairman of Castle Support Services plc until June 2010. He served as the Non-Executive Chairman of Darby Group Plc since 2003 and it's Director since April 25, 2003. Mr. Mills served as a Non-Executive Chairman of Castle Acquisitions Plc and Lonrho Plc. Mr. Mills served as a Director of Denison International plc since 1993. He served as a Director of Quarto Group, Inc. from October 15, 2014 to May 24, 2016. He served as a Director of Baltimore Capital plc since July 28, 2006. He served as a Non-Executive Director of Prime Focus London plc (also known as VTR Plc) from 2003 to October 14, 2011 and Aerte Group plc from January 1988 to December 16, 2008. He was a Director of Stratifer Limited, CCH Advisers Limited, Jarvis Porter (Property Holdings) PLC Limited, Celcis International Limited, Nastor Investments Limited, Harwood Capital LLP, W.G. Mitchell (Fifteen) Limited, W.G. Mitchell (Charlotte Square) Limited, W.G. Mitchell (2005) Limited, W.G. Mitchell (Seven) Limited, W.G. Mitchell (George Street) Limited, W.G. Mitchell Enterprises Limited, Academic Research Limited, Bionostics Limited (in liquidation), and J O Hambro Capital Management Limited. He served as Director of SiRViS IT Holdings Ltd. since March 13, 2007, Worldport Communications, Inc. since June 18, 2003 and NetBank Inc. from November 7, 2006 to August 17, 2007. Mr. Mills was a Non-Executive Director of Paramount Limited. He served as Director of Celsis Group Limited until June 2013, Albany Capital PLC since January 24, 2008, Inspired Gaming Group Limited since September 2006, Acquisitor Plc, Tinopolis Plc, Sterling Construction Co. Inc. since 2001, W-H Energy Services, Inc. since 1990, Hartstone Group Plc from October 14, 2003 to June 25, 2004, D.S. Bancor Inc. since 1988, Langley Park Investment Trust plc, Lonrho Plc and DS Bancor, Inc. since 1988. Mr. Mills was a Non-Executive Director of Tricor Plc from July 1995 to February 3, 2003 and Biome Technologies plc until September 01, 2003. He served as Director of London Trust Productions Limited, Dowding & Mills Plc, Forefront Group Limited, Sirvis IT Limited, Orthoproducts Limited, Sinav Limited, Merchant Properties General Partner Limited, Merchant Properties Nominees Limited, Merchant Properties Two General Partner Limited, Merchant Properties Two Nominee 1 Limited, Merchant ProperRead Full Background




